---
import ToolLayout from '../layouts/ToolLayout.astro';
import ImagesToPdf from '../components/ImagesToPdf.astro';
---

<ToolLayout slug="jpg-to-pdf">
  <ImagesToPdf />

  <div slot="about" class="flex flex-col gap-4 text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-ink-subtle">
    <p>
      This free JPG to PDF converter combines your JPG images (and other formats
      like PNG, WebP, GIF, and BMP) into a single PDF document. Add several images,
      reorder them by dragging (or sort A–Z / reverse), choose a page size (A4,
      Letter, or fit-to-image), an image fit mode, and a margin, then download the
      PDF. Everything runs in your browser — your files are never uploaded.
    </p>
    <p>
      Extra controls let you go beyond the basics: turn on Compress to re-encode
      photos as JPEG at a quality you choose for a smaller file, keep Auto-rotate
      on so photos taken on a phone land the right way up (using their EXIF
      orientation), and pick Fill or Stretch when you want the image to cover the
      whole page instead of fitting inside it.
    </p>
  </div>
</ToolLayout>
